flow.descriptionCdata:
e39c2b76-1b47-43aa-858c-ab941cb05d3b.2df0273b-216a-48fa-a54b-42488dd036c2.description=
Wanted to write a script that handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script example on sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab is running here\:  /data01/clu_direct/${scriptName} ${scriptArgs}

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) inputs\:
device_username	- username -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
device_password	- encrypted password -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

Efficiency\:
checkForNull \= 0.016s
runCLU \= 10.241s
 - Connect to "sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab" and initiate Expect \= 7s
 - Init CLU \= 0s
 - Actual Commands against Router\: 3s
Cleanup .1s
e39c2b76-1b47-43aa-858c-ab941cb05d3b.7c7f3cd1-9c45-4b4e-85e5-9fb65b7cebe4.description=
Operation to check for variables whose values are \=\= "true"

Inputs\:

inputList\:  comma seperated list of variables to check

Reponsses\:
success\:  at least one variable with value of string "true"
fail\:  no vars with a value of string "true"

Result\:  List of variables that have value of sting "true"
e39c2b76-1b47-43aa-858c-ab941cb05d3b.a8164479-36d3-4d81-ad5f-18b1a9a4aec8.description=
Operation to check for null or empty string local variables.

Inputs\:

inputList\:  comma seperated list of variables to check

Reponsses\:
hasNull\:  at least one variable is null or has an empy string for a value
noNulls\:  all variables have a value

Result\:  List of variables that are null or empty strings
e39c2b76-1b47-43aa-858c-ab941cb05d3b.c573f2d7-e4ed-4752-a6bc-3f8e4cf46184.callout=brocade_get_matching_${aliases_or_wwpns}.clu.tcl e39c2b76-1b47-43aa-858c-ab941cb05d3b.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow retrieves alias list (and if any, connected wwpns) that grep a pattern_match

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA), run alishow | grep $pattern_match
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
sanSwitch - IP of Brocade Switch
pattern_match - grep through search.

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias/wwpn information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}
